‘I actually contemplated: ‘Maybe it’s time to stop playing?’ - Former AFC Wimbledon defender Paul Osew opens up on wait for club after landing Welling deal
arts.sum: “The wait between Wimbledon and Northampton – and since I left Woking to join Welling – I actually contemplated: ‘Maybe it’s time to stop playing?’ “When I left Wimbledon, I went to train with Chelsea and Mark Robinson, who was U23s manager at the time.
